===Idiom===
[[Category:English idioms]]
'''until the [[cow]]s come [[home]]'''

====Alternative forms====
'''till the cows come home''', ''''til the cows come home''' (''non-standard'')

#For a very long time.
#:''You can crank the engine until the cows come home, but it won't start without fuel.''

===Usage notes===
*'''Until the cows come home''' functions as an adverb.
*The phrase is frequently used to describe activities that are thought to be [[futile]] or [[unproductive]].

